    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "is not open, binary based patch detection can be used. Natural language processing can be used to lessen human efforts in the partial matching. Errors in the developer logs and patches are threats to validity. We have found some errors in the logs, al- though the number of errors is very small in our evaluation, but it will decrease the accuracy of the method if no additional checks are introduced. Sometimes patches may not be implemented correctly, which means that the software versions are vulnerable even if they are patched. We plan to study how to identify incorrect(incomplete or wrong) patches in the future work.",
