    "text": "(by verifying CVE information with security patches and de- veloper logs based on version tree) and techniques (including partial matching and log tracing methods) to identify the known vulnerable software versions with respect to the CVEs. By comparison of the reports for Linux between our tool and the NVD, we found that there were 11,827 incorrect vulnerable versions of the NVD, and conﬁrmed that 94 patched versions lacked committed records in the changelogs. For future research, it will be interesting to solve the above limitations, and explore whether partial matching and repatching can be extended for binary code vulnerability detection.",
